6:Why partions are required in the topic ?

1: Scalibility :

Maan lo topic me:

Orders

Message1
Message2
Message3
...
Message 10 Billion

Sab ek broker me store hai.

Broker-1
   |
 Orders Topic

over the course of time messages badhte jaenge and ek samay broker ki storage limit reach ho jaegi 

to avoid this we do partioning of topics , topic is just a logical segregation actualy data which belongs to a topic will be present in partions 
using partioning we will be able to scale the system by storing different partions of the topic across mutliple brokers.


2: Parallel Reading

Partition bana diye, lekin usse multiple consumers parallel kaise consume kar lenge?

Aur iska answer hai:

Consumer Group.


=>Sirf Consumer Samjho

Maan lo topic hai: Intro

Aur usme sirf 1 partition hai and Producer bhejta hai:
"MY"
"NAME"
"IS"
"ANURAG"

Partition-0 mai Store hoga:

"MY"
"NAME"
"IS"
"ANURAG"

Yaha pai sirf ek hi partition hai so sabhi messages jo producer ne bheja hai wo sequentially (order preserved) mai partition 0 mai store ho jayega.

Case 1: Sirf 1 consumer hai 

Consumer 1 read karega:

"MY"
"NAME"
"IS"
"ANURAG"

100% ordering maintained. Simple.


Case 2:  Maan lo 2 independent consumers hai

